The paper deals with capacity regions of continuous-time multiuser Gaussian channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the design of multi-user communication systems, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of Brownian motions and capacity achieving modulation/coding schemes suggests a focus on stochastic processes and signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also mentions ultra-wideband communication, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
